<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-26T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="859" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/2–2547: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Peru</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-26T12:00:00-05:00">February
                                    26, 1947—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>95. Council rejects 2–½% top interest rate proposal <gloss target="#t_ur1">ur</gloss> 158 Feb 25.<note n="16" xml:id="d859fn1">Not printed.</note> Question thoroughly canvassed recently.
                                Rogers<note n="17" xml:id="d859fn2">James Grafton Rogers, President
                                of the Foreign Bondholders Protective Council.</note> sure Council
                            members if polled would vote unanimously against it.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>